Reasoning: The paper discusses the design of linear space-time block codes (STBCs) with low-complexity maximum likelihood (ML) decoding using the Sphere Decoder (SD). This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-fields, including information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SI), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), machine learning (cs.LG), and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper's focus on STBCs and their design criteria suggests that cs.IT and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.NI, cs.LG, and cs.MM.
